# Phase 08 Add-to-Cart and E2E Debugging Notes

## Context

Phase 08 expanded testing with a browsing-to-cart E2E flow. The intended flow was:

```text
/products
→ filter for helmet
→ open PeakGuard Helmet detail page
→ add product to cart
→ verify cart drawer opens
→ increase quantity
→ decrease quantity
→ remove item

This phase exposed two different classes of issues:

A real runtime add-to-cart integration issue.
E2E selector strict-mode issues.

Both are useful future references because they show why manual verification and Playwright debugging should be separated.

Issue 1 — Add to Cart Click Did Not Open Cart Drawer
Symptom

Manual testing showed that clicking Add to cart caused status text to appear, but the cart drawer did not open.

Example behavior:

Click Add to cart
→ "PeakGuard Helmet added to cart." text appears
→ cart drawer does not open

This meant the click handler was firing, but the cart drawer state was not being opened.

Diagnosis

Because the status text appeared, the click was reaching the page-level handler.

The missing step was the Pinia cart drawer action:

cartStore.openCart()

The broken behavior was not caused by Playwright. It was a real runtime wiring problem.

Expected Runtime Path
ProductCard or detail Add to cart button
→ page-level handleAddToCart(product)
→ cartStore.addItem(product)
→ cartStore.openCart()
→ cartStore.isOpen becomes true
→ CartDrawer receives open=true
→ AppDrawer renders sidebar
Fix

The page-level add-to-cart handlers were updated to call both:

cartStore.addItem(product)
cartStore.openCart()

The product list handler was reset to:

const handleAddToCart = (product: Product) => {
  cartStore.addItem(product)
  cartStore.openCart()
  lastAddedProductName.value = product.name
}

The product detail handler was also verified to use the same pattern:

const handleAddToCart = (selectedProduct: Product) => {
  cartStore.addItem(selectedProduct)
  cartStore.openCart()
  lastAddedProductName.value = selectedProduct.name
}

For the main product detail add-to-cart action, a native button was used to remove any ambiguity around custom component click forwarding:

<button
  data-testid="detail-add-to-cart"
  class="detail-add-button"
  type="button"
  :disabled="!product.inStock"
  @click="handleAddToCart(product)"
>
  Add to cart
</button>
Verification

Manual testing confirmed:

Product listing Add to cart opens the drawer.
Product detail Add to cart opens the drawer.
Product appears in the drawer.
Header cart count updates.
Subtotal updates.
Quantity controls work.
Remove item works.
Lesson

If a click causes nearby UI text to update but does not trigger the expected global state change, the click handler is probably firing but missing a store action.

Debug in this order:

Confirm the click handler fires.
Confirm local status text updates.
Confirm the Pinia action is called.
Confirm the Pinia state changes.
Confirm the parent shell passes state to the drawer.
Confirm the drawer renders.
Issue 2 — E2E Failed Even After Manual Add to Cart Worked
Symptom

After manual add-to-cart behavior worked, the E2E test still failed.

The first strict-mode error was:

getByText('Specifications') resolved to 2 elements:
1. h2: Specifications
2. caption: Product specifications

The second strict-mode error was:

getByText('PeakGuard Helmet') resolved to 3 elements:
1. Product detail page h1
2. Status text: PeakGuard Helmet added to cart.
3. Cart drawer h3
Diagnosis

These were not app bugs. They were Playwright strict-mode selector problems.

Playwright requires locators to resolve to one element unless .first(), .nth(), or scoped locators are used.

The test was using broad global text selectors even though the same text appeared in multiple parts of the page.

Fix 1 — Use Role Selector for Specifications

Instead of:

await expect(page.getByText('Specifications')).toBeVisible()

use:

await expect(page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Specifications' })).toBeVisible()

This targets the visible heading instead of accidentally matching the table caption.

Fix 2 — Scope Cart Assertions to the Drawer

Instead of globally searching for product text:

await expect(page.getByText('PeakGuard Helmet')).toBeVisible()

scope the assertion:

const drawer = page.getByTestId('cart-drawer')

await expect(drawer).toBeVisible()
await expect(drawer.getByRole('heading', { name: 'PeakGuard Helmet' })).toBeVisible()
Fix 3 — Add Stable Cart Test IDs

To reduce brittle text matching in the cart flow, stable test IDs were added to cart-specific state elements.

Cart item row:

<article :data-testid="`cart-item-${item.product.slug}`">

Cart quantity:

<span :data-testid="`cart-quantity-${item.product.slug}`">
  {{ item.quantity }}
</span>

Cart line total:

<p :data-testid="`cart-line-total-${item.product.slug}`">
  {{ formattedLineTotal }}
</p>

Cart summary:

<dd data-testid="cart-total-items">{{ totalItems }}</dd>
<dd data-testid="cart-subtotal">{{ formattedSubtotal }}</dd>
Final E2E Selector Strategy

Use semantic selectors for user-facing navigation and labels:

page.getByLabel('Search products')
page.getByRole('link', { name: 'PeakGuard Helmet' })
page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Specifications' })

Use test IDs for repeated cart state values:

page.getByTestId('cart-drawer')
page.getByTestId('cart-item-peakguard-helmet')
page.getByTestId('cart-quantity-peakguard-helmet')
page.getByTestId('cart-line-total-peakguard-helmet')
page.getByTestId('cart-total-items')
page.getByTestId('cart-subtotal')
Lesson

When manual behavior works but E2E fails, do not rewrite app logic immediately.

Debug in this order:

Confirm manual behavior works.
Check the exact Playwright error.
Look for strict-mode selector conflicts.
Replace broad text selectors with role/label selectors.
Scope assertions to the relevant container.
Add data-testid only for stable app-state assertions.
Rerun the single failing E2E file before running the full suite.
Final Result

The runtime issue and E2E issue were separate:

Runtime issue:
Add to cart handler did not open Pinia cart drawer state.

E2E issue:
Playwright selectors were too broad and matched repeated text.

The fixes were:

Runtime fix:
Call cartStore.addItem(product) and cartStore.openCart() in add-to-cart handlers.

E2E fix:
Use scoped drawer locators and stable cart test IDs for repeated cart content.

This note should be used as future reference whenever a Vue interaction works partially, or when Playwright strict mode reports multiple matching elements.